20/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The head of the national council for co-operation with The Hague war crimes tribunal, Rasim Ljajic, is travelling to Strasbourg on Monday (December 20th) for talks with Council of Europe (CoE) officials about rapporteur Dick Marty's report on illicit trafficking of human organs in Kosovo.
Ljajic will meet with Deputy Secretary-General of the Council of Europe Maud de Boer-Buquicchio and Commissioner for Human Rights Thomas Hammarberg.
The Committee on Legal Affairs of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe adopted a draft resolution Thursday following Marty's report, calling for an investigation into allegations of human organ trafficking in Kosovo.
(Tanjug, Blic, B92 - 19/12/10)
